Package: llx-external-routing
Version: 0.1-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Eduardo Millan <eduardo.millan@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 35
Depends: iproute2, dnsutils, network-manager, systemd
Section: net
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/eduardomillan/llx-external-routing
Description: Selective domain-based routing for Linux
 Routes traffic for specific domains through an external WiFi interface
 while the rest of the traffic uses the corporate connection by default.
 .
 Features:
  - NetworkManager dispatcher for automatic routing setup
  - Configurable domains and network interfaces
  - Systemd timer for periodic IP refresh
  - Easy configuration via /etc/llx-external-routes/config.conf
